---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro"

const post = {
	title: "Getting Started with Astro Nano",
	date: "2024-03-15",
	author: "Astro Team",
	description:
		"Learn how to build your personal website with Astro Nano, a minimalist template for creators and developers.",
	content: `
    Building a personal website shouldn't be complicated. Astro Nano provides a clean, 
    minimalist foundation for showcasing your work, writing blog posts, and sharing your 
    projects with the world.

    ## Key Features

    - **Blazing Fast**: Built with Astro's static site generation
    - **Minimalist Design**: Focus on your content with clean typography
    - **Markdown Support**: Write content in markdown with full MDX support
    - **Project Showcase**: Beautiful project gallery with filtering
    - **Blog Ready**: Start writing and sharing immediately

    ## Getting Started

    1. Clone the repository
    2. Install dependencies
    3. Customize your content
    4. Deploy to your favorite platform

    The philosophy behind Astro Nano is simplicity without sacrifice. You get all the 
    modern web features you need, wrapped in a clean, maintainable package.
  `,
	tags: ["astro", "web development", "tutorial"],
	readingTime: "5 min",
}
---

<Layout>
	<article class="blog-post">
		<header class="post-header">
			<h1>{post.title}</h1>
			<div class="post-meta">
				<time datetime={post.date}
					>{
						new Date(post.date).toLocaleDateString("en-US", {
							year: "numeric",
							month: "long",
							day: "numeric",
						})
					}</time
				>
				<span class="reading-time">{post.readingTime} read</span>
			</div>
		</header>

		<div class="post-content">
			<div class="post-description">
				<p>{post.description}</p>
			</div>

			<div class="post-body">
				{
					post.content
						.split("\n\n")
						.map((paragraph) => <p>{paragraph}</p>)
				}
			</div>

			<footer class="post-footer">
				<div class="tags">
					{post.tags.map((tag) => <span class="tag">#{tag}</span>)}
				</div>
				<div class="author">
					Written by {post.author}
				</div>
			</footer>
		</div>
	</article>
</Layout>

<style>
	.blog-post {
		max-width: 720px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 2rem 1rem;
	}

	.post-header {
		margin-bottom: 3rem;
	}

	.post-header h1 {
		font-size: 2.5rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
		line-height: 1.2;
	}

	.post-meta {
		color: #666;
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		display: flex;
		gap: 1rem;
	}

	.post-description {
		font-size: 1.2rem;
		line-height: 1.6;
		color: #444;
		margin-bottom: 2rem;
		font-weight: 300;
	}

	.post-body {
		font-size: 1.1rem;
		line-height: 1.8;
		margin-bottom: 3rem;
	}

	.post-body h2 {
		font-size: 1.5rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		margin: 2rem 0 1rem;
	}

	.post-footer {
		border-top: 1px solid #eee;
		margin-top: 3rem;
		padding-top: 2rem;
		display: flex;
		justify-content: space-between;
		align-items: center;
	}

	.tags {
		display: flex;
		gap: 0.5rem;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
	}

	.tag {
		background: #f5f5f5;
		padding: 0.3rem 0.8rem;
		border-radius: 20px;
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		color: #666;
	}

	.author {
		font-style: italic;
		color: #666;
	}
</style>

